quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  24,44,"Allah alternates night and day. Indeed, in that is a lesson for those endowed with sight<i class=""s"">(s) </i>."
  24,45,"And Allah <span class=""h"">created<sup foot_note=""80670"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>every treading creature from water, so of them is one<i class=""s"">(kind) </i>that treads upon its belly, and one<i class=""s"">(kind) </i>that treads upon two legs, and one<i class=""s"">(kind) </i>that treads upon four; Allah creates whatever He wills; Allah is indeed Powerful over everything."
  24,46,"Most surely, We have sent down <span class=""h"">clarifying<sup foot_note=""80671"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>signs{2}, and Allah guides whomever He wills to a straight path.",footnotes:2:The Arabic word used isayat(singularayah). Ayahmeans ‘sign’ or ‘proof’. It is also used to denote the unit of text in the Qur’an,like ‘verse’ in poetry or ‘sentence’ in prose.Each such unit isconsidered a ‘sign’from God.
  24,47,"And they say, “We have attained faith in Allah and in the Messenger, and we have obeyed.” Then a group of them turn away afterwards, for in no way are those ever believers."
  24,48,"And when they are called to Allah and His Messenger in order <span class=""h"">to judge<sup foot_note=""80673"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>between them, a group of them promptly disregards<i class=""s"">(it) </i>;"
  24,49,"but if the truth is in their favor, they come to Him in obedience."
  24,50,"Is there sickness in their hearts? Or have they doubted? Or do they fear that Allah may oppress them, or<i class=""s"">(that) </i>His Messenger<i class=""s"">(may do so) </i>? In fact, they themselves are the unjust."
  24,51,"However, the response of the believers when they are called to Allah and His Messenger in order to <span class=""h"">judge</span><a class=""sup""><sup>c </sup></a>between them has always been to say, “We have heard and obeyed”, for those are the successful."
  24,52,"And whoever obeys Allah and His Messenger and fears Allah and is mindful of Him—then it is those who are the triumphant ones."
  24,53,"And they swore by Allah their most solemn oaths that if you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>commanded them, they would set out. Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Do<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>not swear;<i class=""s"">(your) </i>obedience is well-known{1}. Allah is indeed All-Aware of what you do.”",footnotes:1:Their obedience is well known to be false.
